    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a superlative example of rotary performance. The heart of this machine is a meticulously maintained 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged engine, showing excellent compression across all rotor faces. The power delivery remains linear, with the secondary turbocharger engaging seamlessly at 4,500 RPM. The chassis retains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution, supported by an unmolested double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Every vacuum line has been inspected for integrity to ensure optimal boost pressure. The five-speed manual transmission provides tactile, notch-free shifts, and the undercarriage is free of any fluid seepage or oxidation. This is a mechanically transparent, collector-grade specimen for the discerning enthusiast.",
